value.records-referred: Records Referred at Initial Request Level
value.appeal-base-solely: Appeal Base Solely on Denial of Request for Expedited Processing

value.X1: Protects information that is properly classified in the interest of national security pursuant to Executive Order 12958.
value.X2: Protects records related solely to the internal personnel rules and practices of an agency.
value.X3: Protects information exempted from release by statute.
value.X4: Protects trade secrets and commercial or financial information which could harm the competitive posture or business interests of a company.
value.X5: Protects the integrity of the deliberative or policy-making processes within the agency by exempting from mandatory disclosure opinion, conclusions, and recommendations included within inter-agency or intra-agency memoranda or letters.
value.X6: Protects information that would constitute a clearly unwarranted invasion of personal privacy of the individuals involved.
value.X7a: Protects records or information compiled for law enforcement purposes the release of which could reasonably be expected: to interfere with enforcement proceedings.
value.X7b: Protects records or information compiled for law enforcement purposes the release of which could reasonably be expected: would deprive a person of a right to a fair trial or an impartial adjudication.
value.X7c: Protects records or information compiled for law enforcement purposes the release of which could reasonably be expected: to constitute an unwarranted invasion of the personal privacy of a third party/parties (in some instances by revealing an investigative interest in them).
value.X7d: Protects records or information compiled for law enforcement purposes the release of which could reasonably be expected: to disclose the identity/identities of confidential sources.
value.X7e: Protects records or information compiled for law enforcement purposes the release of which could reasonably be expected: would disclose techniques and procedures for law enforcement investigations or prosecutions.
value.X7f: Protects records or information compiled for law enforcement purposes the release of which could reasonably be expected: to endanger the life or physical safety of an individual.
value.X8: Protects information that is contained in or related to examination, operating, or condition reports prepared by, on behalf of, or for the use of an agency responsible for the regulation or supervision of financial institutions.
value.X9: Protects geological and geophysical information and data, including maps, concerning wells.
